casebody.data:
The State of Ohio, Appellee, v. Caskey, Appellant.

[Cite as State v. Caskey, 126 Ohio St.3d 109, 2010-Ohio-3232.]

(No. 2010-0602 — Submitted June 8, 2010 — Decided July 14, 2010.)

{¶ 1} The discretionary appeal is accepted.

{¶ 2} The judgment of the court of appeals is reversed on the authority of State v. Clayborn, 125 Ohio St.3d 450, 2010-Ohio-2123, 928 N.E.2d 1093, and the cause *110is remanded to the court of appeals for further proceedings consistent with State v. Claybom.

Ron O’Brien, Franklin County Prosecuting Attorney, and Steven L. Taylor, Chief Counsel, Appellate Division, for appellee. Yeura R. Venters, Franklin County Public Defender, and Paul Skendelas, Assistant Public Defender, for appellant. Brown, C.J., and Pfeifer, Lundberg Stratton, O’Connor, O’Donnell, Lanzinger, and Cupp, JJ., concur.
